Simple Interest (SI)= 
P×R×T / 100
​
 
Where:
P = Principal amount (initial money)
R = Annual interest rate (%)
T = Time in years
###simple_interest calculation

principle = float(input("Enter the principle amount:"))
interest_rate = float(input("Enter the annual interest rate: "))
time = int(input("How many years: "))

def calculate_interest(p,r,t):
    return (p*r*t)/100
    
interest_amount = calculate_interest(principle,interest_rate,time)
print("The interest amount is ",interest_amount)
